==== Psychological & Physical Disorders Presenting with Anxiety
- *Psychological Disorders*:

 + Depressive Disorders
 + Substance Use Disorders (especially withdrawal)
 + Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)

- *Physical Disorders*:

 + *Endocrine*: Thyrotoxicosis, Hypoglycemia, Pheochromocytoma
 + *Cardiovascular*: Myocardial Infarction, Arrhythmias
 + *Respiratory*: Pulmonary Embolism, Asthma

==== Scenario: Palpitations, Restlessness, Sweating
*Differential Diagnoses*

+ Panic Attack / Anxiety Disorder
+ Thyrotoxicosis
+ Myocardial Infarction (MI)
+ Hypoglycemia
+ Pheochromocytoma
+ Substance (e.g., caffeine, amphetamine) intoxication or withdrawal.

*Investigations*

+ *ECG*: To rule out MI and arrhythmias.
+ *Thyroid Function Tests (TSH, T3, T4)*: To rule out thyrotoxicosis.
+ *Random Blood Sugar (RBS)*: To rule out hypoglycemia.

